		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My opinion. I believe it's the most correct thing.<br /><br /><strong><span style="font-size: 150%; line-height: normal">Editing in a public notice that the post has been edited.</span></strong><br /><br />Period. Why?<br /><br />a) a moderator/admin has authority for such corrections;<br />b) if the mod/admin is not violating the user's rights, there's no problem of doing it so;<br />c) the user must accept the rules - as editing is something that must be done in a few cases.<br /><br />If the user disagrees, it's easy - go away. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_cool.gif" alt="8-)" title="Cool" />

		

