		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In my view the primary purpose for mods being able to edit posts is so that they can delete things that should not be seen. (e.g. if *dragon were to post psychopathicteen's telephone number, or if someone posted an illegal ROM, etc.). Complete history wouldn't be desired in that case (which should be the only case, IMO, but I already went off at length on that in this thread).<br /><br />You can roll your own version of &quot;history&quot; where needed, though. In forums where I am a mod, I <em>always</em> leave a note in the edit explaining what I did and why, so that everybody knows why moderator action was taken, not just the poster.

		

